erdeen|website=The Telegraph Announcements|accessdate=18 March 2020|date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n**Sir [[John Lyons (linguist)|John Lyons]], 87, linguist.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sir John Lyons 1932\u20132020|url=https://www.trinhall.cam.ac.uk/news/sir-john-lyons/|website=Trinity Hall Cambridge|date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Pete Mitchell (broadcaster)|Pete Mitchell]], 61, English radio DJ and presenter ([[BBC Radio 2]], [[Virgin Radio]]).<ref>{{cite news|title=Pete Mitchell: Former BBC Radio 2 presenter dies aged 61|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-manchester-51879429|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n*14 March \u2013 [[Genesis P-Orridge]], 70, musician ([[Throbbing Gristle]], [[Psychic TV]]) and performance artist ([[COUM Transmissions]]).<ref>{{cite news|last1=Savage|first1=Mark|title=Throbbing Gristle's Genesis P-Orridge dies aged 70|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51893184|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n*15 March \u2013 [[Roy Hudd]], 83, actor (''[[The Blood Beast Terror]]'', ''[[Up the Chastity Belt]]'', ''[[The Alf Garnett Saga]]'') and comedian.<ref>{{cite news|title=Roy Hudd, actor and comic, dies aged 83|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51906543|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*16 March\n**[[David Briggs (headmaster)|David Briggs]], 102, English educator, headmaster of [[King's College School, Cambridge]] (1959\u20131977).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Milmo|first1=Cahal|title=Broadcaster Anne Atkins reveals death of father in 'extraordinary' and 'moving' Thought for The Day|url=https://inews.co.uk/news/broadcaster-anne-atkins-father-death-tribute-radio-4-thought-of-the-day-2482352|website=iNews|date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Mick Morris (footballer, born 1943)|Mick Morris]], 77, English footballer ([[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]], [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]], [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]]).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fielding|first1=Rob|tit