{"title_page": "Fantasmagorie (1908 film)", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name = Fantasmagorie \n| image = Fantasmagorie (Cohl).GIF\n| image_size =\n| caption = A still from the film\n| director = [[\u00c9mile Cohl]]\n| producer = \u00c9mile Cohl\n| writer =\n| starring =\n| cinematography =\n| editing =\n| distributor = [[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 des Etablissements L. Gaumont]]\n| released = {{Film date|1908|08|17|df=y}}\n| runtime = Approx. 1 minute, 20 seconds\n| country = [[France]]\n| language = [[Silent film|None / Silent film]]\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n\n'''''Fantasmagorie''''' is a 1908 [[French film|French]] [[animation|animated]] [[film]] by [[\u00c9mile Cohl]]. It is one of the earliest examples of [[traditional animation|traditional (hand-drawn) animation]], and considered by film historians to be the first [[animated cartoon]].<ref name=\"Beckerman2003\">{{cite book|last=Beckerman|first=Howard|title=Animation: the whole story|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EjW6cCE4v1QC&pg=PA17|accessdate=16 August 2011|date=2003-09-01|publisher=Skyhorse Publishing Inc.|isbn=978-1-58115-301-9|page=17}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\n[[File:Emile Cohl.jpg|thumb|\u00c9mile Cohl]]\nThe film largely consists of a [[stick figure|stick man]] moving about and encountering all manner of morphing objects, such as a wine bottle that transforms into a flower which becomes an elephant. There are also sections of live action where the animator's hands enter the scene. The main character is drawn by the artist's hand on camera, and the main characters are a [[clown]] and a [[gentleman]]. Other characters include a woman in a film theater wearing a large hat with gigantic feathers.\n\nThe film, in all of its wild transformations, is a direct tribute to the by-then forgotten [[Incoherents|Incoherent movement]]. The title is taken from the original French word for \"[[phantasmagoria]]\", a [[Nineteenth Century|mid-Nineteenth Century]] [[magic lantern]] show with moving images of ghosts.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Emile Cohl - Fantasmagorie 1908 - YouTube.theora.ogv|thumb|left|''Fantasmagorie'' (1908)]]\nCohl worked on ''Fantasmagorie'' from February to either May or June 1908. Despite the short running time, the piece was packed with material devised in a [[Stream of consciousness (narrative mode)|stream of consciousness]] style.  The film was released on August 17, 1908.\n\n===Production===\nThe film was created by drawing each frame on paper and then shooting each frame onto [[negative film]], which gave the picture a blackboard look.  It was made up of 700 drawings, each of which was exposed twice (animated \"on twos\"), leading to a running time of almost two minutes. It borrowed from [[J. Stuart Blackton]], the chalk-line effect; filming black lines on white paper, then reversing the negative to make it look like white chalk on a black chalkboard. Blackton and Cohl also borrowed some techniques from [[Georges M\u00e9li\u00e8s]], such as the [[stop trick]].\n\n==See also==\n*''[[Humorous Phases of Funny Faces]]''\n*''[[The Enchanted Drawing]]''\n*[[History of animation]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{bcdb title|47017}}\n* {{IMDb title|0000682|Fantasmagorie}}\n* {{Internet Archive film|id=Fantasmagorie}}\n* {{YouTube|aEAObel8yIE|Emile Cohl - ''Fantasmagorie'' 1908}}\n\n{{Animation industry in France}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fantasmagorie (1908 Film)}}\n[[Category:1900s animated short films]]\n[[Category:1908 films]]\n[[Category:1908 animated films]]\n[[Category:French black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:French animated short films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by \u00c9mile Cohl]]\n[[Category:French short films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:French silent short films]]\n\n\n{{short-animation-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name = Fantasmagorie \n| image = Fantasmagorie (Cohl).GIF\n| image_size =\n| caption = A still from the film\n| director = [[\u00c9mile Cohl]]\n| producer = \u00c9mile Cohl\n| writer =\n| starring =\n| cinematography =\n| editing =\n| distributor = [[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 des Etablissements L. Gaumont]]\n| released = {{Film date|1908|08|17|df=y}}\n| runtime = Approx. 1 minute, 20 seconds\n| country = [[France]]\n| language = [[None / Silent film]]\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n\n'''''Fantasmagorie''''' is a 1908 [[French film|French]] [[animation|animated]] [[film]] by [[\u00c9mile Cohl]]. It is one of the earliest examples of [[traditional animation|traditional (hand-drawn) animation]], and considered by film historians to be the first [[animated cartoon]].<ref name=\"Beckerman2003\">{{cite book|last=Beckerman|first=Howard|title=Animation: the whole story|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EjW6cCE4v1QC&pg=PA17|accessdate=16 August 2011|date=2003-09-01|publisher=Skyhorse Publishing Inc.|isbn=978-1-58115-301-9|page=17}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\n[[File:Emile Cohl.jpg|thumb|\u00c9mile Cohl]]\nThe film largely consists of a [[stick figure|stick man]] moving about and encountering all manner of morphing objects, such as a wine bottle that transforms into a flower which becomes an elephant. There are also sections of live action where the animator's hands enter the scene. The main character is drawn by the artist's hand on camera, and the main characters are a [[clown]] and a [[gentleman]]. Other characters include a woman in a film theater wearing a large hat with gigantic feathers.\n\nThe film, in all of its wild transformations, is a direct tribute to the by-then forgotten [[Incoherents|Incoherent movement]]. The title is taken from the original French word for \"[[phantasmagoria]]\", a [[Nineteenth Century|mid-Nineteenth Century]] [[magic lantern]] show with moving images of ghosts.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Emile Cohl - Fantasmagorie 1908 - YouTube.theora.ogv|thumb|left|''Fantasmagorie'' (1908)]]\nCohl worked on ''Fantasmagorie'' from February to either May or June 1908. Despite the short running time, the piece was packed with material devised in a [[Stream of consciousness (narrative mode)|stream of consciousness]] style.  The film was released on August 17, 1908.\n\n===Production===\nThe film was created by drawing each frame on paper and then shooting each frame onto [[negative film]], which gave the picture a blackboard look.  It was made up of 700 drawings, each of which was exposed twice (animated \"on twos\"), leading to a running time of almost two minutes. It borrowed from [[J. Stuart Blackton]], the chalk-line effect; filming black lines on white paper, then reversing the negative to make it look like white chalk on a black chalkboard. Blackton and Cohl also borrowed some techniques from [[Georges M\u00e9li\u00e8s]], such as the [[stop trick]].\n\n==See also==\n*''[[Humorous Phases of Funny Faces]]''\n*''[[The Enchanted Drawing]]''\n*[[History of animation]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{bcdb title|47017}}\n* {{IMDb title|0000682|Fantasmagorie}}\n* {{Internet Archive film|id=Fantasmagorie}}\n* {{YouTube|aEAObel8yIE|Emile Cohl - ''Fantasmagorie'' 1908}}\n\n{{Animation industry in France}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fantasmagorie (1908 Film)}}\n[[Category:1900s animated short films]]\n[[Category:1908 films]]\n[[Category:1908 animated films]]\n[[Category:French black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:French animated short films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by \u00c9mile Cohl]]\n[[Category:French short films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:French silent short films]]\n\n\n{{short-animation-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hudco123", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed broken link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fantasmagorie_(1908_film)"}
